paragraph, as more important templates will be generated first.
    Each new template contains information indicating whether its constituent templates are obsolete and thus no longer needed.
    Also, at this stage the coverage vector (a data structure that keeps track of which templates have already been combined and which ones are still to be considered in applying operators) is updated to point to the templates that are still active and can be further combined.
    This way we make sure that all templates still have a chance of participating in the actual summary.
    The resulting templates are combined into small paragraphs according to the event or series of events that they describe.
    Each paragraph is then realized by the linguistic component.
    Each set of templates produces a single paragraph.
